The security of a websites information is crucial and there are 
specific regulations in place as per the Canadian Centre for Cyber 
security. The link to the entire PDF of Baseline Cyber Security 
Controls for Small and Medium Organizations can be found below:
https://cyber.gc.ca/en/guidance/baseline-cyber-security-controls-small-and-medium-organizations

The OWASP (Open Web Application Security Project) has created
the Application Security Verification Standard that proposes 
a list of security requirements and controls for web applications
The link to their website is below:
https://owasp.org/

OWASP offers a security API that protects against 
Broken obeject level authorization
Broken user authentication
Excessive data exposure
Lack of resources and rate limiting 
Broken function level authorization
Mass assignment 
Security misconfiguration
Injection
Improper assets management 
Insufficient logging and monitoring 
https://owasp.org/www-project-api-security/

Some other security APIs also include
MCAM Authentication 
OAuth
Postman 
SoapUI